What we’re doing
in the community and around Maritz.









Maritz Awards Arts and Education Council $30,000 for Arts Education Grants
July 10, 2017   |   News Release
 The Arts and Education Council (A&E) announced today that Maritz has generously renewed its support of $30,000 to underwrite the Maritz Arts and Education Fund for Teachers. This distinctive granting program provides opportunities for teachers, schools and non-profit arts organizations to offer programs that encourage creativity in the classroom. 









Maritz Named a Top Workplace by St. Louis Post-Dispatch
June 26, 2017   |   Blog Post
 Great places to work start with amazing people. And, we are excited to announce that we’ve been named a Top Workplace by the St. Louis Post-Dispatch this year because of our great team members. 









St. Louis Startup Attributes Growth to Maritz Mentors
June 23, 2017   |   Blog Post
 As the St. Louis start-up scene continues to grow, we are celebrating success with our partners at Capital Innovators, one of the nation’s top 10 tech accelerators. 






