                            Who We Are
                        












We've been around a long time.






Longevity
In 1894 Edward Maritz started the E. Maritz Jewelry company, a wholesaler and manufacturer of fine jewelry and engraved watches.





Innovation
Reinvention is in our DNA. We pioneered the incentives industry, revolutionized meeting planning, and are transforming customer experiences. In short, we never stop exploring what's next.





People-Focused
It's always been about people for us. Whether you're our client, employee, or a program participant, we value you as a person. It's our strength. And when you work with us, it's yours. 











We're always looking ahead, but we have a very rich history.
– Steve Maritz

















Backed by Science

At our core, we’re a behavior company. The scientific study of human behavior is a central component of Maritz’ DNA, and ingrained in the design of our solutions.
Under the leadership of Chief Behavioral Officer Charlotte Blank, we’re uncovering the latest aha moments in behavioral science and sharing their potential with the modern business world. By connecting our network of leading-edge behavioral science experts and Maritz’ Fortune 500 clients, we’re a catalyst for solving today’s business challenges.
 










Every person can make
                        a difference.
                    
—Brian Bergman, Senior Analyst and Teach for America Maritz Motivation Coach




















Giving Back
in more ways than one.









Education
People drive communities, too. That's why Maritz gives both our dollars and time to educational programs that help children and adults reach their full potential.









Community
We give to non-profit partners who share our values of innovation and results. Together, we make a real impact on our communities. Read our giving guidelines >
Read our community impact report >











Diversity
When businesses focus on diversity, everyone wins. As a St. Louis Minority Business Council member, we’re committed to identifying and strengthening minority and women-owned businesses.









Environment
We want future generations to thrive. And we do our part by reducing waste, water consumption, power usage and paper dependence. We're a St. Louis Green Business Challenge Award Winner.












Leadership
guiding the next 120 years













Steve Maritz
Chairman & CEO







Dennis Hummel
President







Rick Ramos
CFO







Charlotte Blank
Chief Behavioral Officer







Steve Gallant
